simple_message_client(1)          VCS TCP/IP          simple_message_client(1)



NNAAMMEE
       simple_message_client - The VCS TCP/IP message bulletin board client.


SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ssiimmppllee__mmeessssaaggee__cclliieenntt  -s _s_e_r_v_e_r -p _p_o_r_t -u _u_s_e_r [--ii _i_m_a_g_e _U_R_L] -m _m_e_s_-
       _s_a_g_e [--vv] [--hh]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       ssiimmppllee__mmeessssaaggee__cclliieenntt - Send a _m_e_s_s_a_g_e to the VCS TCP/IP  message  bul-
       letin board server ssiimmppllee__mmeessssaaggee__sseerrvveerr(1).

       The  _m_e_s_s_a_g_e  may contain the following HTML tags: <strong>, </strong>,
       <em>, </em>, <br/>.

       For the server either the IPV4 or IPV6 address or a  hostname  must  be
       provided via the _s_e_r_v_e_r option. The TCP port to connect to is given via
       the _p_o_r_t option, which can either be a port number of a service name as
       listed in _/_e_t_c_/_s_e_r_v_i_c_e_s.

       The  user  name  of the message submitter must be provided via the _u_s_e_r
       option. Optionally the URL of an image for the user can be provided via
       the _i_m_a_g_e _U_R_L option.

       In  case the _-_v commandline option is provided, execution trace message
       are written to _s_t_d_o_u_t.

       Providing the _-_h commandline option causes a usage message to be  writ-
       ten to _s_t_d_o_u_t.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       The following options are supported:


       --ss,, ----sseerrvveerr  _s_e_r_v_e_r
              Use _s_e_r_v_e_r (which is either an IPV4 address, an IPV6 address, or
              a hostname) as the server to connect to.


       --pp,, ----ppoorrtt _p_o_r_t
              Use _p_o_r_t (which is either a port number or a  service  name)  as
              the TCP port to connect to. - The range for port numbers is lim-
              ited to [0..65535].


       --uu,, ----uusseerr _u_s_e_r
              Use _u_s_e_r as user name for the message submission.


       --ii,, ----iimmaaggee _i_m_a_g_e _U_R_L
              Use _i_m_a_g_e _U_R_L as URL of an image for the submitting user.


       --mm,, ----mmeessssaaggee _m_e_s_s_a_g_e
              Use _m_e_s_s_a_g_e as message to submit to the bulletin board.


       --vv,, ----vveerrbboossee
              Write execution trace information to _s_t_d_o_u_t

       --hh,, ----hheellpp
              Write usage information to _s_t_d_o_u_t.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       sseerrvviicceess(5), ssiimmppllee__mmeessssaaggee__sseerrvveerr(1), ssiimmppllee__mmeessssaaggee__sseerrvveerr__llooggiicc(1)

